{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were the most barbaric, the most, I mean, blood thirsty, and-- and sadistic guards I'd ever seen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We marched.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't give us anything to eat, sometimes for two days, no drinks, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was one of the coldest winter in '44-- '45 that ever was in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the snow under-- we-- we marched on-- on the main streets, you know, the-- the-- the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the snow was always shoveled to the side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And thirst is worst than famine and hunger.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And if somebody stepped out of the column to grab a handful of snow, they right away shot him, and thousands were shot like this.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Even if he was fast enough to go back and hide, they picked him out, and pulled him by his head and shot him right in front of it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The-- the-- the brain even was-- was-- was flying around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That-- that's what I said when you told me, for example, about what is happening to Muslims, how much they suffer in Bosnia from the Serbs, I said, it's inhuman, but who knows how many of those Bosnians are former SS guards.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Who knows, you see.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, that was my encounter with Muslim SS guards.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we marched about seven weeks, until we came to a small camp on the border between Poland and Czechoslovakia called Reichenbach-- another camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This camp had 20,000 inmates, and they're-- they're all-- I think at that time, out of the 15,000, I doubt it if we were left 7,000, maybe.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They put us there for two, three days, and pepped us up a little bit.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gave us a little bit of food, because sometimes we were sleeping on the ground in winter, in rain and snow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was nowhere to put us.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
